  "text": "Functional mutagenesis of these two cavities showed that cavity B, but not cavity A, is essential for RNA synthesis. The alanine mutation of L328, W859, and I863 in cavity B decreased the initiation of RNA synthesis potentially by affecting formation of the RNA template-RdRp-NTP complex. Furthermore, the K330A mutation abolished viral replication by reducing the NS3/NS5 interaction [CITATION_1] .",
